51 typedef enum
52 {
53  PULSE = 0, // Reset server watchdog.
54  OPEN = 1, // Start up servers.
55  CLOSE = 2, // Close servers and client connection.
56  SETO = 7, // Reset local position to 0,0,0 origin.
57  CONFIG = 18, // Request a configuration SIP.
58  STOP = 29, // Stop the robot; motors remain enabled
59  E_STOP = 55, // Emergency stop; very abrupt by overriding deceleration.
60  STEP = 64, // Single-step mode (simulator only)
61  ARM_INFO = 70, // Request an ARMINFOpac server-information packet
62  ARM_INIT = 72, // Warm-reset the Pioneer Arm
63  ARM_CHECK = 73, // Has Arm servers check to make sure it’s still
64  // responding to commands; reflects in status byte of
65  // ARMpac.
66  ARM_PARK = 76, // Sends all joints to their HOME positions and shuts
67  // power off.
68  SKRMAINT = 117, // Engage Seekur microcontroller maintenance mode
69  // (factory use only).
70  SYSKILL_RECENTER = 119, // Recenter the wheels, then turns off the robot. (Seekur only)
71  RECENTERWHEELS = 120, // Recenter the wheels. (Seekur only)
72  RESET = 253, // Force a power on-like reset of the microcontroller.
73  MAINTENANCE = 255 // Engage microcontroller maintenance (ARSHstub) mode.
74 }Void_t;

76 typedef enum
77 {
78  DIGOUT = 30, // Set (1) or reset (0) User Output ports. Bits 8-15 is
79  // a byte mask that selects, if set (1), the output
80  // port(s) for change; Bits 0-7 set (1) or reset (0)
81  // the selected port(s).
82  VEL2 = 32, // Set independent wheel velocities; bits 0-7 for right
83  // wheel, bits 8-15 for left wheel; in 20mm/sec
84  // increments.
85  PTUPOS = 41, // Set pulse-width for position servo control; lsb
86  // is pulse width in 100μs units; msb addresses
87  // mux'd RC0-4 on Experimenter's Module.
88  ARM_POS = 77, // Sends joint (1st byte) to the position specified
89  // in the 2nd byte, subject to end-limits specified
90  // in FLASH parameters
91  ARM_SPEED = 78, // Delay in milliseconds (2nd byte) between
92  // incremental steps to control the speed and motion
93  // of the joint (1st byte)
94  SEEKURPDB = 116 // Turn a Seekur PDB power port on or off. First byte
95  // indicates which port, second byte indicates state
96  // (1=on, 0=off). See Power Supply for locations of
97  // power output connectors and typical devices
98  // attached to which ports.. Seekur and Seekur Jr. only.
99 }TwoBytes_t;

101 typedef enum
102 {
103  ENABLE = 4, // 1=enable; 0=disable the motors.
104  SETA = 5, // Set translation acceleration, if positive,
105  // or deceleration, if negative; in mm/sec2.
106  SETV = 6, // Set maximum/move translation velocity; mm/sec.
107  MOVE = 8, // Translate (+) forward or (-) back mm distance
108  // at SETV speed
109  ROTATE = 9, // Rotate (+) counter- or (-) clockwise degrees/sec
110  // at SETRV limited speed.
111  SETRV = 10, // Sets maximum/turn rotation velocity; degrees/sec.
112  VEL = 11, // Translate at mm/sec forward (+) or backward (-)
113  // (SETV limited speed).
114  HEAD = 12, // Turn at SETRV speed to absolute heading;
115  // ±degrees (+= counterclockwise).
116  DHEAD = 13, // Turn at SETRV speed relative to current heading;
117  // (+) counter- or (–) clockwise degrees.
118  JOYREQUEST = 17, // Request one or continuous stream (>1) or stop (0)
119  // joystick SIPs
120  ENCODER = 19, // Request one, a continuous stream (>1), or stop (0)
121  // encoder SIPs.
122  RVEL = 21, // Rotate robot at (+) counter- or (-) clockwise;
123  // degrees/sec (SETRV limit).
124  DCHEAD = 22, // Adjust heading relative to last setpoint;
125  // ± degrees (+= ccw)
126  SETRA = 23, // Change rotation de(-) or (+)acceleration, in
127  // degrees/sec2
128  IMUREQUEST = 26, // Use argument value 1 to request one IMU packet.
129  // Use argument value 2 to request continuous IMU
130  // packets every cycle. Send argument value 0 to
131  // stop. See Inertial Measurement Unit (IMU) on
132  // page 53 for details.
133  SONAR = 28, // 1=enable, 0=disable all the SONAR; otherwise, use
134  // bits 1-3 to specify an individual array number 1-4.
135  TIMER = 31, // Initiate user input timer, triggering an event
136  // with specified PIN
137  GRIPPER = 33, // Gripper server commands. See the Gripper or PeopleBot
138  // Manual for details.
139  KICK = 34, // Trigger digital output port OD0 for ms milliseconds
140  // (one-shot).
141  ADSEL = 35, // Selects the A/D port value in standard SIP.
142  GRIPPERVAL = 36, // Gripper server values. See the Gripper or PeopleBot
143  // Manual for details.
144  GRIPREQUEST = 37, // Request one, a continuous stream (>1), or stop (0)
145  // Gripper SIPs.
146  GYROCALCW = 38, // Set the clockwise rotation calibration value for the
147  // gyro accessory.
148  GYROCALCCW = 39, // Set the counterclockwise rotation calibration value
149  // for the gyro accessory.
150  IOREQUEST = 40, // Request one (1), a continuous stream (>1), or stop
151  // (0) IO SIPs.
152  GETAUX = 43, // Request to retrieve 1-200 bytes from the AUX1 serial
153  // port; 0 flushes the buffer.
154  BUMPSTALL = 44, // Stall robot if no (0), only front (1) while moving
155  // forward, only rear (2) while moving backward, or
156  // either (3) bumpers contacted when robot moving in
157  // related direction.
158  TCM2 = 45, // TCM2 module commands; 0=module off, no readings;
159  // 1=compass only, readings in standard SIP; 2=send one
160  // TCM2 packet; 3=send continuous (each cycle) TCM2
161  // packets; 4=user calibration; 5=auto calibration;
162  // 6=stop auto-calibration, send one packet, revert to
163  // mode 1; 7=soft reset
164  JOYDRIVE = 47, // 1=allow joystick drive from port while connected with
165  // a client; 0 (default) disallows.
166  SONARCYCLE = 48, // Change the SONAR cycle time; in milliseconds.
167  HOSTBAUD = 50, // Change the HOST serial port baud rate to 0=9600,
168  // 1=19200, 2=38400, 3=57600, or 4=115200.
169  AUX1BAUD = 51, // Change the AUX1 serial port baud rate (see HOSTBAUD).
170  AUX2BAUD = 52, // Change the AUX2 serial port baud rate (see HOSTBAUD).
171  AUX3BAUD = 53, // Change the AUX3 serial port baud rate (see HOSTBAUD).
172  M_STALL = 56, // Argument 1=MOTORS button off causes a stall
173  GYROREQUEST = 58, // If client-side (HasGyro 1), request one, a continuous
174  // stream (>1), or stop (0) Gyro SIPs. If server-side
175  // (HasGyro 2), 0 disable or 1 to enable the gyro.
176  GETAUX3 = 61, // Request to retrieve 1-200 bytes from the device
177  // connected at the AUX3 serial port; 0 flushes the
178  // buffer.
179  GETAUX2 = 67, // Request to retrieve 1-200 bytes from the device
180  // connected at the AUX2 serial port; 0 flushes the
181  // buffer.
182  CHARGE = 68, // 0=release; 1=deploy autocharge-docking mechanism.
183  ARM_STATUS = 71, // Request one (1), a continuous stream (>1), or stop
184  // (0) ARMpac SIPs.
185  ARM_POWER = 74, // Switches power off (0) or on (1) to all the Arm
186  // servos
187  ARM_HOME = 75, // Sends all (>6) or specified joint (1-6) to the
188  // HOME position
189  ARM_STOP = 79, // Stop the specified (1-6) or all (255) moving
190  // joints
191  ARM_AUTOPARK= 80, // Disable the autopark watchdog (0) or reset it to
192  // some time in seconds other than default
193  // AutoParkTimer in FLASH
194  ARM_GRIPPARK= 81, // Disable the gripper watchdog (0) or reset it to
195  // some time in seconds other than the default
196  // GripperParkTimer
197  ROTKP = 82, // Change working rotation Proportional PID value.
198  ROTKV = 83, // Change working rotation Derivative PID value.
199  ROTKI = 84, // Change working rotation Integral PID value.
200  TRANSKP = 85, // Change working translation Proportional PID value.
201  TRANSKV = 86, // Change working translation Derivative PID value.
202  TRANSKI = 87, // Change working translation Integral PID value.
203  REVCOUNT = 88, // Change working differential encoder count.
204  DRIFTFACTOR = 89, // Change working drift factor.
205  SOUNDTOG = 92, // 0=mute User Control piezo; 1 = enable.
206  TICKSMM = 93, // Change working encoder ticks per millimeter
207  // tire travel.
208  LATVEL = 110, //(Seekur only) Set velocity for sideways translation
209  // (mm/sec). Positive argument values translate to the
210  // right, negative values translate to the left. May be
211  // combined with VEL and RVEL for simultaneous motion.
212  // Maximum speed is limited with SETV and stored firmware
213  // parameter. Only available on Seekur.
214  LATACCEL = 113, // If positive, set acceleration used for LATVEL commands
215  // in mm/sec2. If negative, set deceleration used for
216  // LATVEL commands in mm/sec2.
217  BATTEST = 250, // Artificially set the battery voltage; argument in
218  // tens volts (100=10V); 0 to revert to real voltage
219  DIGTEMPTEST = 251, // Artificially set the digital temperature; argument
220  // in degrees C; 0 to revert to real temperature.
221  ANTEMPTEST = 252 // Artificially set the analog temperature; argument
222  // in degrees C; 0 to revert to real temperature.
223 }Int_t;

225 typedef enum
226 {
227  POLLING = 3, // Change SONAR polling sequence.
228  SAY = 15, // Play up to 20 duration, tone sound pairs through
229  // User Control Panel piezo speaker.
230  TTY2 = 42, // Sends string argument to serial device connected to
231  // AUX1 serial port.
232  LCDWRITE = 59, // Display a message on the LCD accessory: byte
233  // 0=starting column (1-19); byte 1=starting row (1-4);
234  // byte 2=1 if clear line contents first, otherwise 0;
235  // bytes 3- = up to 20 chars, NULL-terminated.
236  TTY4 = 60, // Send string argument out to device connected at AUX3
237  // serial port.
238  TTY3 = 66 // Send string argument out to device connected at AUX2
239  // serial port.
240 }Str_t;
